      <h1>About NodeJs <%=version%> Views</h1>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Views are the user-facing part of the application, in this case, HTML
          files.
        </li>
        <li>
          We use template engines to create our views. As the name suggests, we
          write template files in our codebase that get transformed into HTML
          when we respond to a server request. Any variables defined in our
          template files are replaced with actual data.
        </li>
        <li>
          Additionally, we can insert conditional and/or loop logic into our
          template file, e.g. render the userâ€™s username once they have logged
          in. This would not be possible with plain HTML.
        </li>
      </ul>
